		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2"><a name="110894525738526141"></a><span class="msgSubject">SOE workarounds</span><br clear="all" /><script type="text/javascript">document.title = document.title + ": Thread: SOE workarounds";</script>
		   <span class="sm">Posted: Feb 20th  2005 at  7:18pm EST<span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=13;mid=110894525738526141;num=5;page=1;post=1;replyto=110894525738526141"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a>    | <span class="fs8">Edited: Feb 20th  2005 at  7:22pm EST</span></span></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By: </span><a href="/db/poster.html?user=259987"><span class="Scholar">jonnypanic</span></a><b><span class="Scholar"><br/>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />210 posts
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good  </span><br />
<br/><a href="/db/classes.html?class=13;mid=110894525738526141;page=1;howmany=50#110894525738526141"><img alt="" title="Use this to create a link to this post" src="/shared/garrowrt.png" border="0" height="9" width="11" /> Link to this post</a>

<br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td>
<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>*sigh* <br />You know, I said I wouldn't come back, at least not until more Enchanter issues are addressed. I'm still not coming back, not yet, but I did take the time to look around a bit. It's a shame how little has changed, especially for chanters. <br /> <br />Runes: Group rune for four dots. Yikes. Not only is it a bit harsh for cash-poor players, but the mana cost is extreme, and the runes still don't hold a candle to the melee damage faced by any chanter capable of casting these runes. Or how bout the Epic runes? The 1.5 would be, from what I see, for chanters who raid sometimes, and the 2.0 would be for the hardcore raiding chanter. The melee damage of mobs faced by these kinds of chanters is going to be even greater, yet the runes from the Epics are of un-noteworthy amount. Worse, I'm seeing issues where the little Boggle effect from these runes won't cast if you are doing just about ANYTHING when the rune drops. I've already mentioned how this Boggle effect is too often irrelevant, since the chanter is often the ONLY thing on the mob's hatelist... making it hate you less won't help much when it still hates only you and the tanks are busy elsewhere. I really do believe that it should be at least an AoE hatelist memblur (kinda like FM, except with FM a bard doesn't have to be in range, whereas this effect would be AoE only). <br /> <br />Does anyone else smell workarounds for enchanter surviveability? What's the plan, here, to just keep stacking runes on the chanter? Heck, a rune can't even be compared to, say, a HP buff, because a rune's hps cannot be healed, and if you compare it to a heal, it gets murdered (as a heal, a rune is slow casting, mana- and aggro-intensive, and has a reagent). I'm seeing SOE not really coming up with anything resembling a creative way to help chanters deal with their issues. I just see &quot;Are the chanters still complaining? Well, throw them another rune so we can say we did something.&quot; Some of these runes (noteably, the Epics) aren't even achievable for many chanters. Apparently, increasing chanter survivability by improving mezzes and improving their viability in groups by giving useful group-friendly spells still isn't on the table. <br /> <br />I was never particularly affected by the Charm nerf when I played. I would usually duo outer razorfiends in PoV with a druid or ranger. I do think chanters shouldn't be in control of quad 1k hitting pets, but I also think a simple fix would have been for SOE to simply put lesser mobs in many zones that could be charmed without doing this idiot &quot;charmed damage table&quot; business... maybe include some razorfiend-level mobs in spawn tables of high end zones. Poof! No more (or at least reduced) charm issue. Nevertheless, I do think that, if they insist on reducing charm effectiveness, they should compensate in other areas; a trade in the same field (pets) would be to boost the summoned pets. All I see is barely competitive spells for chanters' new levels, with reduced usage for some lines (a la charm and linked recast timers on some spells), no improvement in other lines, the continuation of at least two largely useless lines (Berserker Spirit runes and dots), and the discontinuation of useful lines like the PBAoE spells. <br /> <br />In the meantime, the only action on the chanter top 10 issues list is work on the Epics, which happened because SOE ended up having to rework ALL the Epics, and the change from considering the rest of the chanter issues to considering the possibility of considering those issues. They're not thinking about them anymore, they're thinking about thinking about them. And, for the first time in over half a year, a Dev has posted in the Station.com chanter forums... and only to comment on a possibly broken illusion spell quest. Like illusions even matter, anymore. <br /> <br />I dunno... I do read that some of the new content is a bit more chanter-friendly, altho' nothing really requires a chanter, and I understand the draw of community (it's the only reason I'm even considering returning right now), but I gotta wonder how many times you people will accept the bones SOE is tossing you before you finally decide you're tired of getting boned. This new expansion, even, looks like a lot of shiny but unnecessary &quot;improvements&quot; as an excuse for another $30-a-pop money grab, instead of needed fixes... SOE really just needs to skip an expansion and spend the time fixing stuff. It's sad that chanters only generally shine in content that's trivial to them at this point. <br /> <br />I just wish I could post this on the Station.com forum, but, without a subscription, I can't. Ah, well. <br /> <br />Game on, and good luck. <br />Jonny Panic <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Sun Feb 20 19:24:31 2005 by jonnypanic</span></i></p>
