<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>First of all, it was proposed that the group enchanter runes would cost 4 peridots. Personally I would have been fine with this, since by the time we get these spells, most of us have enough plat to afford it. The group rune was not made to be something we'd want to use consistantly, only situationally, and for good reason, since it can be used for dare I say powerleveling purposes and people could cast it all day if it didn't hurt to do so. <br /> <br />In any case, that was then. They modified the cost of the spell several times before actually releasing it, and finally settled on it not requiring a reagent, and instead raising the mana cost. Although it is a bit ridiculously high (1400 for the level 60 version alone, absorbs 950) we've always complained because we have so much mana we don't know what to do with it, and now have something. Something nice, for the levels they're given. <br /> <br />The epic rune is stackable with all of our other runes, so I don't think there's much merit in bashing it. <br /> <br />If the epic's AE boggle was a memory wipe instead, all pre-existing aggro that may have been placed on the mob by the tank trying to save your butt when the mob is beating on you would be erased as well. Furthermore if it went off and there were mezzed mobs, they'd in all likelyhood bee-line straight for your cleric as soon as it broke. No thanks, I like the current effect, especially now that they fixed the detrimental flag on it. <br /> <br />You mention runes being slow-casting mana-intensive and aggro-intensive, and having reagents. Targettable runes, yes. 500 mana for a 5-second cast time self-only rune which absorbs 2k in damage is Yes please, and it has no reagent. Never did. As for the aggro thing, rune really isn't That angering. I have never, personally, had a mob turn around and hit me again after losing aggro to a tank simply because I cast the spell. I have heard of this but in my own experience I can't see this being a problem we need to be concerned with, though it may be salt in the wounds to anyone who Has experienced unfortunate issues due to it. <br /> <br />The 'charm nerf' only applies to Omens of War zones from what I've seen. Feel free to correct me if you parsed results on your own but charm kiting in the Halls of Honor as an example has only become more difficult for me because they raised the magic resistance of some Planes of Power zones recently, not because the mob does less damage, or seems to. I will concede that charming mobs around your level in Omens is quite useless however but it has nothing to do with the nerf. Opinions are sure to vary from person to person though. I haven't charmed everywhere I can. I'm too Scared to, and I adore charm soloing outside of that expansion. <br /> <br />I could go on and on picking your post apart but there's really no point. Believe it or not, I'm with you. I don't agree with hardly any of your points but I do agree that the class got the shaft. However, it is not because of what SoE has done or not done to the class. I actually think they have taken several steps in the right direction. <br /> <br />What I think they messed up on was not scaling the class to the content but scaling the content to the class. <br /> <br />For the most part, they could sate the angry masses simply by lowering magic resist, and instead they keep raising it. End of story. I don't post much anywhere because I'm tired of watching this swarm of bees give unrealistic suggestions on how to outright modify the class at some points. It's no wonder no one official listens to most people. They say the devs can't do their job so try to do their job for them. I've heard everything from &quot;Let us wear plate!&quot; to &quot;give us suchandsuch godly spell which isn't so godly in this godly content (OoW, late GoD, etc) but can unbalance the game in simpler content which still is far less than trivial&quot;. <br /> <br />Bleh...</p>
