<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Johnny, <br /> <br />Your scepticism is understood; however, from your previous posts I believe you have taken your disappointment to a whole new level. <br /> <br />The rune thing that you discuss is interesting to say the least. Four dots for a grp rune for a prepatory raid encounter isn't too much to ask from SOE. That rune is designed for raid content with AEs and such, and for nothing more. <br /> <br />The epics are for the raiding enchanter, since it takes a raid to get through some of the fights. Think about when the 1.0 was king, those took a raid too and had nothing more than a clicky and a cool snake head on it. Oh yeah, stats too. It doesn't take a big mental leap to see that the content surrounding these new epics has to be difficult. <br /> <br />In some respects the chanter has gotten the shaft in the new expansions, but not the ones you are bashing on. As Jem said the resistances, specifically the MR have greatly increased, causing more mezzes to be thwarted on the first cast. What I don't see in the new spell line ups is an upgraded Tash line spell, nor have I seen a new slow spell. Something in the code must have been changed to allow us a great ability to still land our Forlorn Deeds after a simple cast of Tash, but still 6 seconds is a little much. True some spells and an aug or effect can lessen the time, but come on...6 seconds? <br /> <br />Look at our color stun series, or what is left of it. That has been faded out and only remains for our amusement while power leveling whole grps in the 30s with our stun locks. Or how about our warrior shadow pet that can dual wield and is 62 level, it actually can take a hit. But, they can't crit like a warrior, even when we stick a Saliks Haste on them to increase the chance of crits. The bug still exists, at least on my server, where you can give two summoned procing weapons to the pet, but only one shows until you either zone or suspend and reactivate the pet. <br /> <br />You speak of survivability. I am here to tell you that the chanter has no problem with the survival rate in high level OOW zones and the like. You do have to work for the abilities in the Alt Adv. but it can be done, I have proven that. I am constantly tanking in BoT with my Cleric wife; and in WoS, there have been many occassion that I am one of the only players standing at the end of a fight, along with the cleric. We have no problems to speak of. We certainly can't expect SoE to hand our power to us on a platter. They certainly have made the abilities for us to where we can take a few hits and still effect a positive outcome in the engagement. <br /> <br />I see no work-arounds that you speak of, they have made it so that if we want to take a hit we have to earn it. These are the same people that nerfed the taunt ability to 50% and increased hate AAs to tanking classes. They simply have to earn the ability to taunt mobs now rather than having it handed to them at level 1. <br /> <br />Charms suck any way you cut it. It is because of us chanters who misused the charming ability in the first place that allowed it to gain negative attention. I am not one of those chanters that charm killed groupable mobs and then turned around and sold the loot at an inflated price, but it sure did happen. Some may have even exploited a bug allowing them the ability to kill an otherwise unsoloable mob. We did it to ourselves on that one. I do not agree with the charmed mobs damage dropping, but for sake of another solution that was probably the fastest and most exact way to fix the power we could employ. <br /> <br />We, or maybe I should say, I, never expected my class to be one of those highly sought after classes that a group could not live without. It is true that we make a group's experience that much more safer, but that comes at a price. We are a misunderstood class to most. Most see us as nothing more than buffers and debuffers then we sit. They don't see us behind the screen with three-way timers for mez. They don't see us target assisting only to switch off of it to mezz an add. They can't understand why we freak out when a mezzed mob has been rudely woke up a second after mezz stuck the vermin.  <br /> <br />In the face of all that, we employ great power and great skill in the fantasy realm of Norrath. Play or don't play. The game is really what us chanters make it and nothing more. If we suck and don't put in the time to better our abilities then we run the risk of tarnishing our class image; but if we take the time, we shine that dull gray and change many a mind to our truly awesome powers that many never knew we had. <br /> <br />-Prost <br /> <br />You know you are powa when you can stick 12 mobs and duo kill them slowly...</p>
